## WHAT I DID

- Stood up a tiered Vitest harness with three opt-in scopes: `tests/unit/` (the always-on CI gate), `tests/integration/` (env-gated against a real Supabase test DB), and `tests/rls/` (env-gated, two authed clients). Reworked `vitest.config.ts` and added `test:unit` / `test:integration` / `test:rls` / `test:all` scripts. Aliased `server-only` to a stub so server modules can be unit-tested in Node.
- Added shared helpers in `tests/_helpers/`: env detection (`env.ts`), service-role / anon / asUser client factories (`supabase-clients.ts`), and a test-user lifecycle that creates auth + mirror rows and tears them down via cascade (`test-users.ts`).
- **Unit tests for authorization (50 tests, all passing):**
  - `tests/unit/auth-gate.test.ts` — every branch of `requireAuth` and `requireCompanionMode` (401 unauthenticated, 403 missing mirror row, 500 mirror lookup error, 200 success, 409 `companion_mode_required`) with mocked Supabase client.
  - `tests/unit/profile-validators.test.ts` — every zod validator in `app/api/profiles/_lib/validators.ts` (rate/radius/coordinate/headline/bio bounds, meal-type allow-list, time and timezone format, availability ordering, partial-patch semantics, photo path bounds, UUID format).
  - `tests/unit/api-errors.test.ts` — `apiError` envelope and HTTP status mapping (frozen contract).
  - `tests/unit/parse-json-body.test.ts` — `parseJsonBody` malformed-JSON and ZodError paths.
  - `tests/unit/enums-transitions.test.ts` — `BOOKING_NEXT_STATES` and `REQUEST_NEXT_STATES` invariants (no skipping `confirmed`, terminal states never revive).
- **Integration tests for `/api/profiles` (17 tests, skip-clean without env):** `tests/integration/profiles.test.ts` exercises companion-profile insert/update with CHECK enforcement (rate, radius), public-view RLS gating (verified vs unverified), availability CRUD with `availability_window_order` and FK-violation paths, ordered listing, cascade on profile delete, photo path round-trip, and the `companion_profiles_verified_at_set` constraint as a defense against client-driven self-verification.
- **RLS policy tests (16 tests, skip-clean without env):** `tests/rls/policies.test.ts` pins every policy on `users`, `companion_profiles`, and `availability` — owner-only select/insert/update/delete, the verified-companion discovery toggle, and an anonymous-read denial sweep on `messages` / `payments` / `bookings` / `meal_requests`.
- Wired CI: existing `.github/workflows/ci.yml` runs `npm run test`, which now executes the unit suite — fast, deterministic, no test DB required. Integration + RLS jobs need a TEST_SUPABASE_* secret set; that's flagged below.
- Committed as `phase-1(qa): tiered test harness, unit + integration + rls suites` (e2484bf).

